cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with routing in wireless ad hoc networks. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper mentions the use of channel gains and statistical characterization of nodes in the routing scheme. 
3. cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a possibility as the paper discusses distributed solutions for routing. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper uses a model of the physical layer and considers the performance of different routing schemes. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses optimization problems and presents sub-optimal routing schemes with lower computational complexity.
